{
  "text": "So-called 'every' properties of algebraic datatypes are introduced by Jensen in [CITATION_1] to characterise those recursive data structures in which every element fulfils some requirement. For example, for lists of integers, one uniform property is that every element of the list must be non-negative. More generally, if we consider lists then, given a requirement r on the elements of a list l , the combinator every(r )(l ) is defined as follows",
